<p>When run aplication on my android phone, geolocation not working. Also in task bar icon GPS is not visible.</p>  <p>Use Visual studio 2015 and Apache Cordova</p>  <p>Index.html</p>  <pre><code>document.addEventListener("deviceready", onDeviceReady, false); function onDeviceReady() {     navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(onSuccess, onError); } function onSuccess(position) {      var elementLantitude = document.getElementById('txtLantitude');     var elementLongitude = document.getElementById('txtLongitude');     elementLantitude.innerHTML = 'Latitude: ' + position.coords.latitude;     elementLongitude.innerHTML = 'Longitude: ' + position.coords.longitude; } </code></pre>  <p>Also in AndroidManifest.xml is added:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" /&gt; &lt;uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" /&gt; &lt;uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_LOCATION_EXTRA_COMMANDS" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In Config.xml  is added --> <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/01Lai.png" rel="nofollow">http://i.stack.imgur.com/01Lai.png</a></p>